---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BrandBranchesGrid from '../../components/BrandBranchesGrid.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE, MAIN_PHONE_TEL } from '../../data/branches';

const title = "True Residential Built-In Refrigerator Repair | Southern California | Anaheim";
const description = "True Residential built-in refrigerator repair Southern California — TBR column, commercial-grade engineering. Anaheim CA 70k sqft factory LA-local parts. $89 diagnostic. (424) 325-0520.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/true-residential-built-in-refrigerator-repair/";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "What is True Residential and how does it differ from True Manufacturing commercial?",
    a: "True Manufacturing is a St. Louis Missouri commercial refrigeration manufacturer founded in 1945 — the dominant US commercial foodservice refrigeration OEM serving restaurants, bars, grocery, and institutional foodservice across the country. <b>True Residential</b> is True Manufacturing's residential spin-off, launched in 2003, bringing commercial-grade engineering to luxury residential built-in refrigeration. The residential line is manufactured at a dedicated 70,000 square foot facility in Anaheim California — the LA-local factory proximity is a practical service advantage (Gap #47 commercial-grade-residential factory-adjacent pattern, similar to Hestan Anaheim + F&P Huntington Beach LA-local). True Residential products bring commercial-spec compressor + condenser unit engineering, 8-year residential warranty on major components, and commercial-grade service-life expectation in a residential-form-factor built-in refrigerator. The parent True Manufacturing commercial line is separate scope from SDAR residential service; we service True Residential only on this page."
  },
  {
    q: "What True Residential built-in models are common in LA luxury kitchens?",
    a: "True Residential's built-in lineup centers on column architecture with commercial-grade engineering. <b>TBR Built-In Refrigerator</b> — 30\" + 36\" + 48\" column refrigerator + side-by-side configurations in stainless or panel-ready integrated finish. <b>TMR Mini Refrigerator</b> — undercounter integrated refrigerator for kitchen islands + butler's pantries + secondary zones; 15\" + 24\" widths. <b>TUR Undercounter Refrigerator</b> — 24\" undercounter with drawer or door configurations. <b>TWC Wine Cellar / Wine Cooler</b> — matched-column wine storage. <b>True Residential color program</b> — distinctive matte color options (not just stainless) give True a recognizable design-forward aesthetic; LA luxury kitchens often install True Residential for the color-program flexibility where Sub-Zero or Miele don't offer comparable color variants. LA install concentration: Bel Air + Beverly Hills + Brentwood custom luxury remodels, Manhattan Beach + Palos Verdes coastal luxury, Silver Lake + Los Feliz design-forward where the commercial-industrial aesthetic is the design direction, Pacific Palisades + Malibu architectural custom."
  },
  {
    q: "How does Anaheim factory proximity help True Residential service in LA?",
    a: "True Residential operates a 70,000 square foot manufacturing facility in Anaheim California — approximately 30 miles from central LA and within same-day driving distance for LA-authorized service. The factory-proximity advantage parallels Hestan (Anaheim), Fisher &amp; Paykel (Huntington Beach), and Capital (Santa Fe Springs) on LA-local CA-luxury manufacturing — collectively the Gap #47 commercial-grade-residential factory-adjacent pattern. Practical impact on True Residential service: (1) common parts availability typically 1-3 day to LA-authorized service vs 5-10 day on mainland-US-distribution luxury brands; (2) specialty components + color-program matched-finish parts often factory-sourced same-day when stock permits; (3) legacy-generation OEM parts continuity supported by factory proximity + True Residential's 8-year residential warranty commitment. For LA luxury households that prioritize service-economics speed alongside luxury-brand positioning, True Residential's Anaheim-local factory is a meaningful practical advantage."
  },
  {
    q: "True Residential commercial-grade engineering — what does that mean for repair?",
    a: "True Residential brings three commercial-derived engineering characteristics to residential refrigeration. <b>(1) Commercial-spec compressor architecture</b> — Embraco or True-specified compressors rated for commercial-duty-cycle service; longer useful life + better performance under high-ambient conditions (LA summer kitchen temperatures are a real refrigeration stress factor that commercial-grade compressors handle better). <b>(2) Commercial-spec condenser unit</b> — larger condenser surface area + higher-capacity fan motor than typical residential-grade units; runs cooler + longer-service-life. <b>(3) Commercial service-access principles</b> — condenser + compressor access through front panel routing designed for field service rather than lifetime-installed architecture common on residential-only designs. Practical service impact: parts pricing is slightly higher than residential-only brands reflecting commercial-grade component costs; service-life expectation extends 20-25+ years on primary components with proper maintenance; warranty coverage (True Residential's 8-year residential warranty) is more generous than typical luxury-residential brand coverage. For households prioritizing long-service-life refrigeration, True Residential is engineered specifically for that outcome."
  },
  {
    q: "What does True Residential built-in refrigerator repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Residential diagnostic $89 waived with repair. Common True Residential built-in service bands: temperature sensor NTC $260–$340; water inlet valve $280–$380; ice maker module $360–$480 (commercial-grade module); evaporator fan motor $340–$480 (commercial-spec motor); defrost heater + thermostat $340–$460; door gasket $300–$440 per section; compressor start relay + capacitor $280–$400 (commercial-grade components); compressor replacement $950–$1,500 including refrigerant recharge (commercial-grade compressor pricing); main control board $440–$680; display board $340–$500; panel-overlay gasket (integrated) $340–$480; color-matched panel replacement quoted individually (color-program matching + Anaheim factory lead time). True Residential service economics run at the upper-luxury tier reflecting commercial-grade component costs; typical 10-20% above mainstream-luxury on parts pricing, offset by Anaheim factory proximity advantage on lead time (1-3 day typical vs 5-10 day on mainland-distribution luxury). For households running True Residential in multi-unit installs (refrigerator + wine cellar + undercounter as suite), multi-appliance service visits schedule efficiently through Anaheim factory-local parts channel."
  },
  {
    q: "Is True Residential worth the premium vs Sub-Zero / Miele / Thermador?",
    a: "Depends on buyer priority. True Residential's differentiators: <b>(1) commercial-grade engineering</b> with 8-year residential warranty (longer than most luxury-brand coverage) and 20-25+ year service-life expectation on commercial-spec compressor + condenser; <b>(2) LA-local Anaheim factory</b> giving parts-chain speed advantage over mainland-US-distribution luxury brands; <b>(3) color program</b> flexibility for design-forward kitchens where Sub-Zero / Miele / Thermador don't offer comparable color-matched options; <b>(4) commercial pedigree</b> with True Manufacturing's 80-year restaurant-refrigeration heritage translating to residential durability. Trade-offs vs Sub-Zero / Miele / Thermador: True Residential is less established in the luxury-brand recognition hierarchy; pricing sits comparable to Sub-Zero mid-range but below Sub-Zero flagship + Miele MasterCool + Liebherr Monolith on ultra-premium column; resale value consideration in LA luxury-kitchen market tends to favor Sub-Zero recognition despite True Residential's engineering merit. For households prioritizing engineering fundamentals + LA-local service economics + design flexibility, True Residential is a strong alternative; for households prioritizing established luxury-brand recognition + resale value, the traditional Sub-Zero / Miele / Thermador choice prevails."
  }
];

const schemaJsons = [
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "LocalBusiness", "@id": canonical + "#business",
    "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair — True Residential Built-In Refrigerator Service",
    "image": "https://samedayappliance.repair/images/same-day-appliance-repair.png",
    "url": canonical, "telephone": MAIN_PHONE_TEL, "priceRange": "$$$$",
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ]
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Service", "serviceType": "True Residential Built-In Refrigerator Repair",
    "provider": { "@id": canonical + "#business" },
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ],
    "description": "True Residential built-in refrigerator repair across Southern California — LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, Riverside. TBR column (30/36/48 stainless + panel-ready integrated), TMR Mini Refrigerator, TUR Undercounter, TWC Wine Cellar. Commercial-grade engineering from True Manufacturing St. Louis 1945; residential manufactured Anaheim CA 70k sqft since 2003. $89 residential diagnostic waived with repair.",
    "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "priceSpecification": { "@type": "PriceSpecification", "price": "89.00", "priceCurrency": "USD", "description": "Residential diagnostic fee, waived with repair" } }
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({ "@type": "Question", "name": f.q, "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a } })) },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Brands", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "True Residential", "item": canonical },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "Built-In Refrigerator Repair", "item": canonical }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <Fragment slot="head-scripts">{schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}</Fragment>
  <div class="call-banner"><div class="wrap"><span>True Residential built-in service? Same-day across all 5 SoCal counties:</span><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="phone-lg">{MAIN_PHONE}</a></div></div>

  <section class="hero"><div class="wrap">
    <div class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/brands/">Brands</a> › True Residential › Built-In Refrigerator Repair</div>
    <h1>True Residential Built-In Refrigerator Repair</h1>
    <p class="lede">True Residential brings commercial-grade refrigeration engineering to luxury residential built-in — the residential spin-off of True Manufacturing (St. Louis, Missouri since 1945; dominant US commercial foodservice refrigeration OEM). Manufactured at a dedicated 70,000 square foot facility in Anaheim California since 2003, True Residential delivers commercial-spec compressor + condenser engineering, commercial-grade 8-year residential warranty, and 20-25+ year service-life expectation in luxury residential built-in form factor. Product lineup covers TBR Built-In Refrigerator column (30"/36"/48" in stainless or panel-ready integrated), TMR Mini Refrigerator undercounter (15"/24"), TUR Undercounter Refrigerator (24" drawer + door), and TWC Wine Cellar matched-column wine storage. LA-local Anaheim factory proximity (approximately 30 miles from central LA) delivers parts-chain speed advantage — typical 1-3 day parts availability to LA-authorized service vs 5-10 day on mainland-US-distribution luxury brands. LA install concentration: Bel Air + Beverly Hills + Brentwood custom luxury, Manhattan Beach coastal, Silver Lake + Los Feliz design-forward, Pacific Palisades architectural. Same-day dispatch, $89 residential diagnostic waived with the repair.</p>
    <div class="hero-cta"><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="btn btn-primary">Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a><a href="#book" class="btn btn-ghost">Request a Visit</a></div>
    <ul class="hero-facts">
      <li><b>True Manufacturing St. Louis since 1945</b> — residential spin-off 2003</li>
      <li><b>Anaheim CA 70,000 sq ft factory</b> — LA-local 1-3 day parts typical</li>
      <li><b>Commercial-grade engineering</b> — 8-year residential warranty, 20-25+ yr service life</li>
      <li><b>$89 residential diagnostic</b> — waived when you authorize the repair</li>
    </ul>
  </div></section>

  <BrandBranchesGrid />

  <section class="trust-bar"><div class="wrap"><span>CSLB #1138898 · Insured</span><span>Same-day in 5 SoCal counties</span><span>Residential diagnostic $89 · waived with repair</span></div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>True Residential built-in lineup we service</h2>
    <p>True Residential's built-in catalog organizes around four main product lines. <b>TBR Built-In Refrigerator</b> is the flagship column line — 30\" + 36\" + 48\" refrigerator column + side-by-side configurations available in stainless finish or panel-ready integrated for custom cabinetry acceptance; commercial-grade compressor + condenser engineering in residential form factor. <b>TMR Mini Refrigerator</b> covers undercounter integrated refrigerator format for kitchen islands + butler's pantries + secondary-zone refrigeration (15\" + 24\" widths). <b>TUR Undercounter Refrigerator</b> covers 24\" undercounter refrigerator in drawer or door configurations. <b>TWC Wine Cellar / Wine Cooler</b> covers matched-column wine storage for wine-enthusiast kitchens running wine cellar alongside refrigerator column.</p>
    <p>True Residential's <b>color program</b> offers matte color options (graphite, blue, green, orange, and custom color-match) beyond traditional stainless — giving True a distinctive design-forward aesthetic not available from Sub-Zero / Miele / Thermador / Liebherr in comparable form factors. Color-program panels are factory-matched at Anaheim production with typical 2-4 week lead on specialty color orders. For service on color-matched units, exterior-panel protection discipline matters — we identify color + finish at intake and route service access through refrigerator cavity when possible to preserve exterior finish. Parts chain via Anaheim factory + True Residential authorized service network supports current production + all legacy generations back through 2003 launch.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Common True Residential built-in failures our techs see in LA</h2>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Not cooling — commercial-grade condenser clean</h3><p>Commercial-spec condenser still requires periodic maintenance despite larger surface area. Deep clean $120–$180 resolves most 'not cooling' without parts.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Temperature sensor NTC drift</h3><p>5-8 year service item. Per-section sensor swap $260–$340; verify sensor vs control board before escalating.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Ice maker + water inlet valve</h3><p>Commercial-grade ice maker module $360–$480; water inlet valve $280–$380. Components rated for higher-duty-cycle than typical residential.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Door gasket compression loss</h3><p>Per-section gasket $300–$440 at 10-15 year mark. European-spec profile on color-matched units requires specific OEM.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-group"><h3>Color-matched panel service</h3><p>Exterior panel damage on color-program units requires Anaheim factory-matched replacement. 2-4 week lead typical; quoted individually.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Commercial-grade compressor longevity</h3><p>Commercial-spec Embraco / True-specified compressors typically 20-25+ year service life. Compressor replacement $950–$1,500 (commercial-grade parts pricing) rare pre-20-year.</p></div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Anaheim factory proximity — Gap #47 commercial-grade-residential pattern</h2>
    <p>True Residential's Anaheim California 70,000 square foot manufacturing facility places the brand in a distinctive LA-local CA-luxury manufacturer cluster alongside <b>Hestan</b> (Anaheim factory since 2014), <b>Fisher &amp; Paykel</b> (Huntington Beach LA-local parts distribution), and <b>Capital</b> (Santa Fe Springs manufacturing) — collectively the commercial-grade-residential factory-adjacent pattern we track as Gap #47. LA-local factory proximity delivers three practical service advantages: (1) parts-chain speed — typical 1-3 day common-component availability vs 5-10 day on mainland-US-distribution luxury brands; (2) specialty parts sourcing — Anaheim factory can supply color-matched panels, specialty-finish hardware, legacy-generation OEM parts without extended backorder lead; (3) multi-unit install servicing — for LA luxury households running multi-unit True Residential suites (refrigerator + wine cellar + undercounter), multi-appliance service visits schedule efficiently through Anaheim factory-local parts channel. For households selecting luxury built-in with LA service-economics as a decision factor, the Gap #47 CA-local manufacturer cluster (True + Hestan + F&amp;P + Capital) is a meaningful practical differentiation vs East Coast or European mainland-distribution luxury brands.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>What True Residential built-in refrigerator repair typically costs</h2>
